================================================================================
Command                  Description
===========              ===========
H                        HELP.

H command                Help on command.  Example "h st".

ST                       Status.

P port# port#            Port assignment. Example "p 1a 1b".

M port# portList         Multicast port assignment.  Example "m 1a 1b1c1d2b".

CC portList portList     Complex connect.  Example "cc 1a1b 2a2b 3a3b"

================================================================================
HELP SCREEN.
================================================================================
================================================================================
LX1500e (NTS) COMMANDS
  ___________________________ROUTING_________________________________________
AL [Loop# [Plist [out]]]                      Auto-Loop (with auto-bypassing)
CC [Plist [..Plist]] | [Plist r|out]          Complex Connect
M  Port# [Plist [out]]                        Multicast (input)
OE [Plist [out]]                              Output (laser) Enable control
P  Port# [Port#]                              Port configuration
SL [Loop# [Plist [out]]]                      SCRAMNet Loop
S  Port# [Port#]                              SCRAMNet port configuration
  ___________________________STATUS___________________________________________
ST [d | v | l]                                Status (signal detects / loops)
  _______________________CONFIGURATION________________________________________
BC [pc|pf [n# text]] | [vr|vs|vsl] |          Box Configuration and setup
   [tm [time]] | [cs|cr n#] | [pw password] | [x text]
UI [am |be |ec |vt |vb |dw |pr n#]            User Interface configuration
  ____________________________________________________________________________
   Port# - port ID e.g. 1a                    Plist - list of ports e.g. 1a2c5d
   Loop# - loop ID e.g. 23                    n# - numeric value e.g. 0
   Type h comand_name for details             Type h 1,2,3,4 for all notes

================================================================================
COMMAND REFERENCE.
================================================================================
================================================================================
AL - Auto-Loop, SL - SCRAMNet Loop (with auto-bypassing) setup

   al [Loop# [Plist [out]]]
   sl [Loop# [Plist [out]]]        - for SCRAMNet loop

DESCRIPTION
   Adds/removes ports to/from the loop. Port auto-bypassing feature is
   activated. Without optional parameters it returns the loop status.

OPTIONS
   out   - reverse action switch (remove rather than add).

EXAMPLES
   al5 1a2b3c4d - add ports 1a, 2b, 3c, and 4d to loop 5.
   al5          - show members of loop 5 e.g. L05=1a2b4d 3c (active ports
                  listed first.
   al           - returns all currently configured loops
   al6 all      - places all ports on loop 6.
   al6 1a out   - removes port 1a from loop 6 and places it in wrap mode.
   al6 all out  - removes only ports currently configured on Loop# 6 (AL06).

NOTES
   Switch <out> will place listed ports in internal loopback (wrap) mode.
   If sl is substituted in the above examples, only SCRAMNet info is returned.

================================================================================
BC - Box Configuration

   bc pc [n# text]    - user port card information display or update
   bc pf [n# text]    - factory port card information display or update
   bc tm [time]       - time (and date) display or update
   bc vr              - firmware version
   bc vs|vsl          - vital statistics for the session or lifetime
   bc cs|cr n#        - active configuration save or recall (from n# bank)
   bc pw password     - locks/unlocks factory configuration fields
   bc x text          - echo host-generated pattern for synchronization

DESCRIPTION
   Returns or sets information or settings.

NOTES
   See individual helps for help concerning a specific command by typing:
  "h bc xx" where xx is a command from the list above.

================================================================================
CC - Complex Copy configure

   cc [Plist [..Plist]] | [Plist r|out]

DESCRIPTION
   In its regular form, for every Plist, cc connects output of given port to
   input of the next port on the Plist. The last port output gets connected to
   the input of the first port on Plist. In its 'r' form cc will accept a
   Plist consisting of 32 ports only. Input of a port specified on the list
   will connect to the output of a port determined by the position on the Plist.
   Out places all ports in PList in internal loopback mode.

EXAMPLES
   cc 3a3b 6a7b8a   - sets two independent loops with 2 and 3 ports.
   cc 3a3b7d...4c r - conects output of port 1a to input of 3a, output of 1b to
      input of 3b, output of 1c to input of 7d,... output of 8d to input of 4c.
   cc 1a2b2c1b out  - sets 1a, 2b, 2c, and 1b into internal loopback mode.
   cc               - returns routing vector e.g. 1a1a1a1a7b7c7d7a......3a4a.

NOTES
   Very little if any error checking is provided.  Without a PList, an
   appropriate status vector is returned.  Port auto-bypass feature is
   deactivated for all affected (output) ports.

================================================================================
M - Multicast (input) configure

   m Port# [Plist [out]]

DESCRIPTION
   Configures Multicast routing of the specified port or returns the multicast
   routing vector.

EXAMPLES
   m1a 1a2b3c4d - adds ports 1a 2b 3c 4d to multicast list of port (input) 1a.
   m1a          - returns a list of all the ports (outputs) copying signal from
                  port 1a input - e.g. M1a=1a1b2b3c4d7d.
   m2a all      - multicasts 2a to all 32 ports
   m1a 1a2b out - removes ports 1a 2b from multicast list of 1a and places them
                  in internal loopback (wrap) mode.

NOTES
   Ports listed with <out> switch will be placed in wrap mode only if they are
   copies of the Port#.

================================================================================
OE - Output (transmiter/laser) Enable control

   oe [Plist [out]]

DESCRIPTION
   Turns laser  ransmitter accordingly for all the ports from Plist. Without
   parameters the laser state vector is displayed representing the state of
   all transmitters (bit set to 1 if enabled). By default all lasers will be
   turned on when LX1500e boots regardless of prior shutdown states.

EXAMPLES
   oe 1a2b3c4d - turns laser of 1a, 2b, 3c, and 4d on.
   oe          - returns the status of all lasers e.g. OE=fff61fff.
   oe 1a6b out - turns laser of 1a and 6b off.

NOTES
   OE command will enable/disable signal routing on any port card. Active
   laser operation (on and off) requires appropriate port card.

================================================================================
P - Port (output),  S - SCRAMNet port (output) configure

   p Port# [Port#]
   s Port# [Port#]    -  for SCRAMNet ports

DESCRIPTION
   Modify the configuration of a port.
   If only the first Port# is specified the status of the port is returned

EXAMPLES
   p4a 4c - configures port 4A as a copy of 4C.
   p4a    - returns the status of 4a.
   s5a 5c - configure port pair 5a-5b a copy of the port pair 5c-5d.

NOTES
   See application notes for more information on the returned status.

================================================================================
P - Port (output),  S - SCRAMNet port (output) configure

   p Port# [Port#]
   s Port# [Port#]    -  for SCRAMNet ports

DESCRIPTION
   Modify the configuration of a port.
   If only the first Port# is specified the status of the port is returned

EXAMPLES
   p4a 4c - configures port 4A as a copy of 4C.
   p4a    - returns the status of 4a.
   s5a 5c - configure port pair 5a-5b a copy of the port pair 5c-5d.

NOTES
   See application notes for more information on the returned status.

================================================================================
