================================================================================
ST - Status

   st [d|v|l]

DESCRIPTION
   Displays the switch status and/or signal detects.

OPTIONS
   []- State of all ports including routing and signal detect information.
       See application notes for help reading the returned status.
   d - The signal detect vector in hex form e.g SD=00FFFFFe. The leftmost bit
       corresponds to port 1a and the rightmost bit corresponds to port 8d.
   v - Positional vector of signal detects with port code present if its input
       detects signal and "__" otherwise.
   l - Positional vector of port loop assignments. Loop ID present if the port
       is configured in the loop and "__" otherwise.

EXAMPLES
   st d - returns the signal detect vector e.g. SD=ffff1f00.
   st v - returns signal detect vector e.g. SV=1a1b_1d__...__8c8d.
   st l - returns loop assignment vector e.g. LA=01__1224__01...__23.

NOTES
   ST without parameters is not recommended in computer-driven applications.

================================================================================
UI - User Interface Configuration

   ui [am|be|ec|vt|vb|dw|pr n#]

DESCRIPTION
   Sets multiple and mostly static user interface options.

OPTIONS
   am  - auto-messaging (formerly ds - display signal), n#={0,1,2,8}
   be  - beeping, n#={0,1}
   ec  - echo host characters, n#={0,1}
   vt  - VT100 escape codes, n#={0,1}
   vb  - verbose level, n#={0,1,8} 
   dw  - display window, n#={0,1,2,3,4}
   pr  - display window update period, n#={10 to 300} seconds.

EXAMPLES
   ui      - returns status vector with all the option values
   ui dw 0 - turns display window off.

NOTES
   General rule: n#=0 turns a feature off. Use ui option_name for more help.
